    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect errno usage in fapi_nvIPC epoll functions\n\n### Summary\nFixed incorrect errno usage where errno was checked after intervening calls that could overwrite it downstream of function create_recv_thread in nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_nvIPC.c.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_nvIPC.c`: \n  - Removed duplicate errno.h include\n  - Fixed errno usage in epoll_create1 error handling by immediately capturing errno value\n  - Fixed errno usage in epoll_ctl error handling by immediately capturing errno value  \n  - Improved epoll_wait errno handling logic to properly preserve errno values\n  - Added proper resource cleanup on errors\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/fapi_nvIPC.h`: Created header file with function declarations\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/aerial/CMakeLists.txt`: Added build configuration for aerial FAPI components\n\nThe fixes ensure that errno values are captured immediately after system calls fail and are preserved for proper error reporting, addressing potential issues where error information could be lost due to intervening function calls overwriting errno.\n\n"
}